     NNNNooootttteeeessss
          _X_l_r_8_s_e_t does not verify the presence of the 256K or RAM on
          the XLR8er adapter.  The presence of the 256K of RAM is
          assumed unless you use the ----1111 option.

          _X_l_r_8_s_e_t will not install the patches if any of the following
          conditions exist:  (an error message will be displayed)
                1.    The HD64180/Z180 CPU was not detected.
                2.    There is insufficient memory available in the
                      low-memory driver area.  Try running _x_l_r_8_s_e_t
                      before loading filters and character drivers
                      since they can usually operate in high memory.
                      The _f_o_r_c_e_h_i(U1) utility can help you force
                      filters and drivers into high memory.
                3.    The patches are already present, either
                      permanently applied to the files or added by
                      _x_l_r_8_s_e_t.  If _x_l_r_8_s_e_t has already been run since
                      the system was booted and the patches were
                      loaded then, _x_l_r_8_s_e_t will not try to load them
                      again.
                4.    The base system does not have 128K of RAM
                      installed.
                5.    The operating system is not LS-DOS 6.3.0 or
                      6.3.1.  Any other operating system may require
                      different patches.


